  "local_port": 53042,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Can we know if our card has been inserted in ATM?",
  "response": "Yes, you can typically know if your card has been inserted into an ATM through a few methods:\n\n1. **Visual Confirmation:** When you insert your card into the ATM, it usually goes into a slot and remains partially visible or gets pulled in completely. If it's pulled in completely, there's often a beep or a message on the screen confirming that the card has been accepted.\n\n2. **On-Screen Prompt:** Most ATMs will display a message on the screen once the card is inserted correctly. This message usually prompts you to enter your PIN or select a language.\n\n3. **Beep or Sound:** Many ATMs emit a beep or another sound to indicate that the card has been successfully inserted.\n\n4. **Card Reader Light:** Some ATMs have a light near the card reader that may change color or start blinking to indicate that the card has been inserted.\n\n5. **Physical Resistance:** If the card is inserted correctly, you'll feel a bit of resistance as the ATM grips the card. If you can pull it out easily, it might not be fully inserted.\n\nIf you're unsure whether your card has been inserted correctly, you can gently try to pull it out. If the ATM has accepted it, the card should not come out easily. If you encounter any issues, it's best to contact your bank for assistance.",
